5 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Improved customer service -- direction to department -- report to
6 legislature. (1) To streamline the Montana medicaid program application and renewal process, the department
7 shall accept:
8 (a) applications, renewals, recertifications, and periodic reports online and by phone; and
9 (b) required document submissions electronically, including via upload from a mobile device.
10 (2) (a) The department shall use text messaging and e-mail to communicate with members and
11 applicants who provide cell phone numbers and e-mail addresses.
12 (b) The department shall establish a system to notify members and applicants via text message
13 and e-mail when verifications are due and when a renewal, recertification, or periodic report is due.
14 (3) (a) The department shall provide a phone hotline for members and applicants. The hotline may
15 also be used for other public assistance benefits.
16 (b) The department shall provide an expected wait time and offer a callback option to each hotline
17 caller.
18 (4) The department shall allow a member to submit an online or a printed renewal form during a
19 90-day reconsideration period if the member's coverage under the Montana medicaid program is terminated for
20 procedural reasons.
21 (5) The department shall set a target ex parte renewal rate of no less than 60% of the total
22 Montana medicaid population by June 30, 2026. An ex parte renewal is a renewal conducted pursuant to 42
23 CFR 435.916(b)(1).
24 (6) (a) Client-facing technology implemented after [the effective date of this act] must have optimal
25 functionality on cell phones, tablets, and computers.
26 (b) The department shall modify existing client-facing technology to ensure optimal functionality on
27 cell phones, tablets, and computers by June 30, 2026.
28 (7) All written application notices and application or renewal forms must be:
- 2 - Authorized Print Version – ****

