69th Legislature 2025 LC1217.1
1 (a) written in plain language consistent with requirements of 42 CFR 435.905(b) and 42 CFR
2 457.110(a); and
3 (b) translated into the state's five most commonly spoken languages.
4 (8) The department shall report on a quarterly basis to the children, families, health, and human
5 services interim committee, in accordance with 5-11-210, on issues related to medicaid client service, including:
6 (a) the total number of applications and renewals;
7 (b) ex parte renewal success rates, including:
8 (i) total renewals and percentage by coverage group;
9 (ii) data sources used;
10 (iii) monthly compliance with federal requirements; and
11 (iv) steps the department is taking to reach the target set in subsection (5);
12 (c) the percentage of applications and percentage of renewals submitted online, in person, by
13 mail, and by phone;
14 (d) the percentage of applications and percentage of renewals completed within 24 hours, 7 days,
15 30 days, 45 days, 60 days, and 90 days;
16 (e) hotline call volume at the state and county level, including wait times and answer rates; and
17 (f) the number of individuals whose medicaid-related mail is returned to the department as
