22 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Client advisory board -- duties -- membership. (1) (a) There is a client
23 advisory board, composed of individuals who are currently or have been enrolled as members in the Montana
24 medicaid program and individuals with direct experience supporting Montana medicaid program members.
25 (b) The department shall establish a selection process to appoint members of the board and
26 publish this information on the department’s website.
27 (c) The board must be composed of at least seven members selected by the director of the
28 Montana medicaid program and must include:
- 3 - Authorized Print Version – ****

****
69th Legislature 2025 LC1217.1
1 (i) at least three current or former Montana medicaid members;
2 (ii) at least two individuals who have direct experience supporting a family member, including a
3 child or family member with a disability, with enrolling in the Montana medicaid program and navigating
4 medicaid services; and
5 (iii) at least two individuals who serve as a paid or unpaid caregiver for a Montana medicaid
6 program member.
7 (d) Board members must be selected for 2-year terms.
8 (e) At least two members of the client advisory board must be appointed to the state’s medicaid
9 advisory council, as required under 42 CFR 431.12.
10 (2) (a) The board shall meet at least quarterly to advise the department on the experience of
11 Montana medicaid program members and effective medicaid program administration.
12 (b) The department shall solicit feedback from the board regarding:
13 (i) new services and changes to services;
14 (ii) care coordination;
15 (iii) quality of services;
16 (iv) eligibility, enrollment, and renewal processes;
17 (v) beneficiary and provider communications by the department;
18 (vi) cultural competency, language access, health equity, disparities, and biases in the Montana
19 medicaid program;
20 (vii) access to services; and
21 (viii) other issues that impact the provision of medical care services in the Montana medicaid
22 program and health outcomes for medicaid members.
23 (3) (a) The department shall provide staff support to the board.
24 (b) The department shall establish a meeting schedule and format to maximize participation,
25 including ensuring members of the board can participate remotely.
